WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:12.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.631 --> 00:32.999
- [snoring]

00:33.066 --> 00:34.401
[crash, glass breaks]

00:34.467 --> 00:35.869
What was that?

00:35.935 --> 00:39.406
Are those rascals Fee and Foo
staying up late again?

00:39.472 --> 00:41.074
Looks like it's time
to talk to them

00:41.141 --> 00:43.843
about the importance
of eight-hour sleep cycles.

00:43.910 --> 00:45.345
Again.

00:45.412 --> 00:48.314
Fee? Foo?
You guys awake?

00:49.549 --> 00:50.550
Hup!

00:50.617 --> 00:51.951
Ow!

00:52.018 --> 00:53.253
- Harvey, could you
keep it down?

00:53.319 --> 00:54.654
We're trying to sleep.

00:54.721 --> 00:57.724
- Wait, you guys weren't making
all that noise?

00:57.791 --> 00:59.058
{\an1}- What?
No, man.

00:59.125 --> 01:01.261
{\an1}You keep telling us
we need to go to bed early.

01:01.327 --> 01:05.465
- But if it wasn't you...

01:05.532 --> 01:07.467
[all snoring]

01:07.534 --> 01:08.468
- Huh...

01:08.535 --> 01:09.869
[glass breaks]

01:09.936 --> 01:11.137
- Sounds like it's coming
from the kitchen.

01:11.204 --> 01:15.742
- Okay, get some sleep,
Michelle.

01:15.809 --> 01:17.911
- Over here!

01:17.977 --> 01:18.912
{\an3}- Whoa!

01:18.978 --> 01:20.113
- A little bit to the left!

01:20.180 --> 01:22.682
{\an1}Yes, my left
is your left too!

01:22.749 --> 01:25.418
We are facing the same way!

01:25.485 --> 01:26.686
- Aww.

01:26.753 --> 01:27.687
- Hey, guys!

01:27.754 --> 01:29.756
What are you doing?

01:29.823 --> 01:31.524
{\an3}- Aaah, mission failed!
Abort!

01:31.591 --> 01:32.592
- What?

01:32.659 --> 01:33.593
{\an3}- Abort.

01:33.660 --> 01:34.794
- A boat?

01:34.861 --> 01:35.962
{\an3}- A-bort!

01:36.029 --> 01:37.063
- You're bored.

01:37.130 --> 01:38.998
- Ah! Abort!

01:39.065 --> 01:41.734
- A bird!

01:41.801 --> 01:42.869
- Whatever.
Run away!

01:42.936 --> 01:45.505
[all chatter]

01:45.572 --> 01:48.508
<i>[jazz music]</i>

01:48.575 --> 01:55.515
<i>♪</i> ♪

01:55.582 --> 01:58.518
- [yelling indistinctly]

02:00.887 --> 02:01.855
- But, Boss--

02:01.921 --> 02:04.390
{\an3}- No!

02:04.457 --> 02:06.192
{\an3}[grunts]

02:06.259 --> 02:08.527
- No, no Papa Jean, no!

02:08.595 --> 02:10.029
Please!
Not zat.

02:10.096 --> 02:13.466
Not...ze stink eye!

02:13.533 --> 02:15.869
Oh, the shame!

02:15.935 --> 02:17.337
It burns!

02:17.403 --> 02:19.472
How can we call ourselves
criminals

02:19.539 --> 02:23.610
when we can't even steal
a single jar of peanut butter?

02:23.676 --> 02:25.979
Comrades, we must repent.

02:26.045 --> 02:28.982
<i>[somber music]</i>

02:29.048 --> 02:30.683
<i>♪</i> ♪

02:30.750 --> 02:32.151
{\an1}- Yikes.
This is sad.

02:32.218 --> 02:34.420
- Yeah, it is.

02:34.487 --> 02:35.522
{\an1}Excuse me.

02:35.588 --> 02:38.124
{\an1}Sorry, I didn't mean
to eavesdrop.

02:38.191 --> 02:39.692
Did you guys want this?

02:39.759 --> 02:41.094
You can have it.

02:41.160 --> 02:44.230
{\an1}My parents can just buy
some more with my allowance.

02:44.297 --> 02:46.132
- Ooh, how dare you!

02:46.199 --> 02:47.767
We are hardened criminals!

02:47.834 --> 02:49.402
We do not accept charity.

02:49.469 --> 02:51.337
We spit on your peanut butter.

02:53.873 --> 02:54.908
- Oh, gosh!

02:54.974 --> 02:56.442
I didn't mean to insult you!

02:56.509 --> 02:57.877
- Well, you did!

02:57.944 --> 03:00.680
Now get out of here
before we get really offended.

03:00.747 --> 03:02.048
- Okay, okay.

03:02.115 --> 03:04.450
Don't shoot.

03:04.517 --> 03:05.785
{\an1}- Geez.

03:05.852 --> 03:06.920
Those guys are jerks
even when you're trying

03:06.986 --> 03:08.121
to do something nice for them.

03:08.187 --> 03:09.289
- Can I have that?

03:09.355 --> 03:11.324
- Yeah, they were pretty rude.

03:11.391 --> 03:14.360
But I still can't help
but feel bad for them.

03:14.427 --> 03:16.162
- But they're a bunch of crooks.

03:16.229 --> 03:18.531
- Even crooks have feelings,
Fee.

03:18.598 --> 03:20.867
{\an1}- The squirrels only feel good
when they're being bad.

03:20.934 --> 03:22.735
{\an1}But they're so bad
at being bad.

03:22.802 --> 03:24.370
{\an3}- Hmm.

03:24.437 --> 03:27.040
{\an3}Then we just got to find someone
who's good at being bad

03:27.106 --> 03:29.008
so they can get their bad back.

03:29.075 --> 03:30.677
- Uh, what?

03:30.743 --> 03:33.513
- And I know just the guy.

03:34.614 --> 03:37.550
[thudding]

03:40.019 --> 03:41.487
- [sighs]

03:41.554 --> 03:44.090
- Le sigh.

03:44.157 --> 03:46.392
- What the--?
Who goes there?

03:49.362 --> 03:50.863
- The name's Bootsy.

03:50.930 --> 03:53.266
[bell dings]

03:54.867 --> 03:56.869
Bootsy St. Claire.

03:56.936 --> 03:58.271
<i>- Sacre bleu!</i>

03:58.338 --> 04:00.139
You didn't even ring
the doorbell.

04:00.206 --> 04:02.875
You're obviously not a good guy!

04:02.942 --> 04:03.876
- You got that right, bub.

04:03.943 --> 04:05.311
- [gasp]

04:05.378 --> 04:06.412
And now you're going to eat
that sandwich

04:06.479 --> 04:09.716
with your elbows on ze table?

04:09.782 --> 04:10.817
[all gasp]

04:10.883 --> 04:12.852
- You are a crazy man.

04:12.919 --> 04:15.121
Have you ever heard of manners?

04:15.188 --> 04:17.156
- Manners?
Heh heh.

04:17.223 --> 04:18.825
Yeah, right.

04:18.891 --> 04:21.793
{\an1}You don't need manners when
you're a criminal mastermind.

04:21.861 --> 04:23.096
You see this scar?

04:23.162 --> 04:24.697
{\an3}- You mean the heart
on your face?

04:24.764 --> 04:28.134
- I got it
'cause I love crime so much.

04:28.201 --> 04:30.269
[all gasp]

04:30.336 --> 04:32.872
- I came to you
because I need your help.

04:32.939 --> 04:35.074
- Ah!
Ooh la la.

04:35.141 --> 04:36.709
- Not that kind of help.

04:36.776 --> 04:38.378
I mean a heist.

04:38.444 --> 04:39.746
And word on the street is,

04:39.812 --> 04:42.515
you're the biggest crooks
on campus.

04:42.582 --> 04:44.550
- Oh, I don't know, Bootsy.

04:44.617 --> 04:48.655
The last time we tried to steal
something we failed hardcore.

04:48.721 --> 04:52.592
- Cut that out!
Get over here.

04:52.659 --> 04:55.161
{\an1}You want to know what I see
when I look at you?

04:55.228 --> 04:57.096
I see a team of awful,

04:57.163 --> 05:00.266
{\an1}unrighteous villains
of the law.

05:00.333 --> 05:03.336
- Wow, do you really mean that,
Bootsy?

05:03.403 --> 05:04.570
- Of course, man.

05:04.637 --> 05:07.173
{\an3}- Alright countrymen,
what do you say?

05:07.240 --> 05:08.808
Are we back in ze game?

05:08.875 --> 05:12.145
[all cheering]

05:12.211 --> 05:13.880
{\an1}- All right,
let's get started.

05:13.946 --> 05:16.215
Here's the plan.

05:16.282 --> 05:18.251
<i>Our target's code name</i>
<i>is "hat head".</i>

05:18.317 --> 05:19.752
<i>And word on the street,</i>

05:19.819 --> 05:20.953
<i>he's pretty loose</i>
<i>with his peanut butter.</i>

05:21.020 --> 05:22.689
[knocking on door]

05:22.755 --> 05:26.259
<i>Also, he definitely has not</i>
<i>been bribed to let us rob him.</i>

05:26.325 --> 05:27.260
-<i> Oh, good!</i>

05:27.326 --> 05:28.961
<i>I am glad to hear it.</i>

05:29.028 --> 05:30.930
-<i> Anyways, I've been casing</i>
<i>his pad for weeks</i>

05:30.997 --> 05:33.966
<i>and he always leaves</i>
<i>his kitchen window unlocked.</i>

05:34.033 --> 05:35.735
<i>And from there,</i>
<i>it's a straight shot</i>

05:35.802 --> 05:39.172
<i>to that big old jar</i>
<i>of Nutshell Drip.</i>

05:39.238 --> 05:40.406
- The what?

05:40.473 --> 05:43.376
{\an1}- You know.
That sweet and salty mud.

05:45.044 --> 05:46.479
The liquid legume.

05:48.381 --> 05:49.482
Peanut butter.

05:49.549 --> 05:51.584
{\an3}[all gasp,
chatter excitedly]

05:51.651 --> 05:53.820
<i>♪</i> ♪

05:53.886 --> 05:56.589
- All right, guys,
just like we planned.

05:56.656 --> 05:59.992
Jean Claude!
Scope out the area.

06:00.059 --> 06:02.495
Amazing cartwheel, bud.

06:02.562 --> 06:05.364
There she is, the big mama.

06:05.431 --> 06:07.400
- I don't know about zis,
Bootsy...

06:07.467 --> 06:11.237
{\an1}If we get caught,
I--I don't think I can handle

06:11.304 --> 06:12.538
the humiliation.

06:12.605 --> 06:14.774
{\an3}- You cut that out right now,
Mister!

06:14.841 --> 06:16.142
You can do this.

06:16.209 --> 06:18.044
Bootsy believes in you.

06:18.111 --> 06:20.747
{\an3}Anyway, you don't have to worry
about that hat head.

06:20.813 --> 06:23.149
{\an3}That guy's
completely distracted.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.617
- ♪ La la la la la ♪

06:24.684 --> 06:27.153
Talking on my phone
with all my many friends.

06:27.220 --> 06:28.721
So distracting!

06:28.788 --> 06:32.125
- Oh! Your confidence
gives me life, Bootsy!

06:32.191 --> 06:36.262
It is time to commence
Operation: Peanut Butter.

06:36.329 --> 06:39.265
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:39.332 --> 06:42.635
<i>♪</i> ♪

06:42.702 --> 06:45.138
- Oh, look.
There's a ladder.

06:45.204 --> 06:46.205
{\an1}<i>Victoire!</i>

06:46.272 --> 06:50.943
[cheering]

06:51.010 --> 06:52.178
- Nice job, guys!

06:52.245 --> 06:54.347
We got the goods
so let's amscray.

06:54.413 --> 06:58.117
[chattering excitedly]

06:58.184 --> 06:59.719
- [gasps]
<i>Incroyable.</i>

06:59.786 --> 07:02.688
{\an1}Bootsy, we have hit
ze jackpot!

07:02.755 --> 07:03.923
Take it all!

07:03.990 --> 07:05.291
- H--hold on a sec!

07:05.358 --> 07:06.659
Just because we're criminals

07:06.726 --> 07:09.162
doesn't mean we have to
get greedy, right?

07:09.228 --> 07:10.363
How are we even going to manage

07:10.429 --> 07:12.265
to carry all that
peanut butter?

07:12.331 --> 07:15.067
{\an3}- Uh, Billie Jean is
a strong woman.

07:15.134 --> 07:16.068
- Oh!

07:16.135 --> 07:17.270
- Mm-hmm.

07:17.336 --> 07:19.105
- Zis is amazing!

07:19.172 --> 07:20.606
Thank you, Bootsy! Oh!

07:20.673 --> 07:23.476
None of zis would have been
possible without you!

07:23.543 --> 07:26.512
- Heh, yeah, huh.

07:26.579 --> 07:27.713
- [humming to himself]

07:27.780 --> 07:28.881
- Hey, Moff.

07:28.948 --> 07:31.317
{\an1}- Ah!
How's everything going in there?

07:31.384 --> 07:33.586
- Umm, it's going pretty good.

07:33.653 --> 07:35.488
{\an3}The squirrels are having
a lot of fun.

07:35.555 --> 07:36.923
- Well, how nice.

07:36.989 --> 07:40.293
It feels good to help people,
doesn't it?

07:40.359 --> 07:41.694
- I'm glad you feel that way,

07:41.761 --> 07:43.629
because the squirrels
are helping themselves

07:43.696 --> 07:47.600
to the rest
of your peanut butter.

07:47.667 --> 07:51.170
- Stop right there,
you greedy little vermin.

07:51.237 --> 07:52.672
both: Ah!

07:52.738 --> 07:57.410
- That's my personal property
you're stealing!

07:57.476 --> 07:59.278
- You're ze greedy one,
old man.

07:59.345 --> 08:00.847
Fire!

08:00.913 --> 08:01.881
[machine whirs]

08:01.948 --> 08:05.184
- Augh!

08:05.251 --> 08:06.419
- Oh, boy.

08:06.485 --> 08:08.421
{\an3}- Do you think we hatched
out of eggs?

08:08.487 --> 08:09.755
{\an1}<i>- Fee! Foo!</i>
<i>Come in!</i>

08:09.822 --> 08:11.624
- Hey man,
how's the plan goin'?

08:11.691 --> 08:14.594
- Not good.
It's a bloodbath over here.

08:14.660 --> 08:16.929
- Stop stealing my stuff!

08:16.996 --> 08:18.097
{\an1}D'oh!

08:18.164 --> 08:19.665
- I don't know what to do.

08:19.732 --> 08:22.134
- Don't worry, dude.
We'll take care of it.

08:22.201 --> 08:23.636
<i>- You want what now?</i>

08:23.703 --> 08:25.705
{\an3}- We need to borrow
all your weapons and cop stuff

08:25.771 --> 08:28.174
so we can stop a robbery.

08:28.241 --> 08:31.577
Uhh, please or whatever.

08:31.644 --> 08:33.511
- Victory is ours, nerd!

08:33.578 --> 08:34.513
Now let's grab the loot
and get out of here.

08:34.580 --> 08:35.982
[siren wails]

08:36.048 --> 08:38.384
<i>- This is the police.</i>
<i>Come out with your</i>

08:38.451 --> 08:39.784
hands in the air.

08:39.852 --> 08:43.121
We've got you surrounded,
suckas!

08:43.188 --> 08:45.591
{\an3}- This probably isn't
what Harvey wanted.

08:45.658 --> 08:47.260
- This isn't what I wanted!

08:47.326 --> 08:48.628
- Holy Crepe Suzette!

08:48.694 --> 08:50.930
The police!
What are we going to do?

08:50.997 --> 08:53.065
[panicked chattering]

08:53.132 --> 08:55.067
- There is no escape.

08:55.134 --> 08:56.369
Wait! Bootsy!

08:56.435 --> 08:57.937
You can get us
out of this, right?

08:58.004 --> 09:00.539
- Uh, I wasn't really
expecting this,

09:00.606 --> 09:03.009
but I think you're
a great criminal.

09:03.075 --> 09:05.478
I'm sure you could
come up with a plan.

09:05.544 --> 09:06.846
- Really?

09:06.913 --> 09:08.848
- Come on, boss,
lead the way!

09:08.915 --> 09:13.786
- [sniffs] Oh Bootsy, your faith
in me has given me strength.

09:13.853 --> 09:15.855
I think I have got a plan!

09:15.922 --> 09:19.025
But we'll probably have to
kill the hostage.

09:19.091 --> 09:20.293
- What?

09:20.359 --> 09:21.594
- All right, criminals,

09:21.661 --> 09:23.663
{\an3}I'm giving you
to the count of 500

09:23.729 --> 09:26.799
to get your no good keisters
out of here!

09:28.968 --> 09:29.735
What?

09:29.802 --> 09:31.470
A bunch of ugly hats?

09:31.537 --> 09:33.439
Now that don't make no sense.

09:33.506 --> 09:37.343
- Now!

09:37.410 --> 09:39.545
- An ambush?
Ugh! Ah!

09:39.612 --> 09:41.013
- Ah!
Careful!

09:41.080 --> 09:43.983
I had two breakfastses
this morning!

09:44.050 --> 09:45.952
- Sean Jean!
Give Bootsy some cover.

09:46.018 --> 09:49.188
Jean Claude!
More acorns on ze right.

09:49.255 --> 09:50.489
- Why, I oughta--

09:50.556 --> 09:52.825
Oh, no you did not--unh!
That's it!

09:52.892 --> 09:55.728
I'm just gonna buh-zap
the biggest target I see!

09:55.795 --> 09:56.762
Buh-zap!

09:56.829 --> 09:59.265
- Oh, no no no!
Oh!

09:59.332 --> 10:02.134
- Ha!

10:02.201 --> 10:04.437
- Oh what a day.

10:04.503 --> 10:08.274
[all cheering]

10:08.341 --> 10:09.742
- Oh!

10:09.809 --> 10:11.344
I can't remember the last time
I felt ze rush

10:11.410 --> 10:13.012
of pulling off a heist!

10:13.079 --> 10:15.982
You must come with us
to present zis to Papa Jean!

10:16.048 --> 10:17.216
- You go on, squirrels.

10:17.283 --> 10:19.485
{\an1}It's about time
for old Bootsy St. Claire

10:19.552 --> 10:20.753
to hit the road.

10:20.820 --> 10:23.189
- You--you are leaving us?

10:23.255 --> 10:27.126
- You know why Operation: Peanut
Butter was a success, Jean Luc?

10:27.193 --> 10:28.561
Because of you.

10:28.627 --> 10:29.595
All of you.

10:29.662 --> 10:31.464
You don't need me anymore.

10:31.530 --> 10:33.866
My work here is done.

10:33.933 --> 10:35.234
- I understand.

10:35.301 --> 10:37.136
Good-bye, Bootsy.

10:37.203 --> 10:40.506
- I think you mean...

10:40.573 --> 10:43.075
bad-bye.

10:43.142 --> 10:47.146
[bell dings]

10:47.213 --> 10:48.347
- To Bootsy!

10:48.414 --> 10:50.883
[all cheer]

10:50.950 --> 10:54.086
- [chatters indistinctly]

10:55.221 --> 10:56.522
- A little to ze left.

10:56.589 --> 10:57.790
Zere!

10:57.857 --> 10:59.158
Perfect.

10:59.225 --> 11:02.161
{\an3}- We will never forget you,
Bootsy St. Claire.

11:02.228 --> 11:04.897
And your help
in our time of need.

11:04.964 --> 11:07.700
Because of you,
we now have the confidence

11:07.767 --> 11:10.903
to proceed with our next crime:

11:10.970 --> 11:14.573
ze elimination of Harvey Beaks!

11:20.613 --> 11:22.982
<i>- ♪ I am the sum</i>
<i>of many parts ♪</i>

11:23.049 --> 11:24.383
<i>♪ Right from the start ♪</i>

11:24.450 --> 11:26.285
<i>♪ I knew not where to begin ♪</i>

11:26.352 --> 11:30.856
<i>♪ They were opening</i>
<i>my eyes up ♪</i>

11:30.923 --> 11:32.391
<i>♪ I'm like the stars</i>
<i>that fall ♪</i>

11:32.458 --> 11:34.093
<i>♪ Without the wherewithal ♪</i>

11:34.160 --> 11:36.629
<i>♪ To let the wind</i>
<i>come back in ♪</i>

11:36.695 --> 11:41.434
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:41.500 --> 11:44.370
<i>♪ I bet I'll find the pieces ♪</i>

11:44.437 --> 11:45.571
<i>♪ That will fit ♪</i>

11:45.638 --> 11:48.340
<i>♪ And make me right, polite ♪</i>

11:48.407 --> 11:52.645
<i>♪ Despite my scalded heart ♪</i>

11:52.711 --> 11:55.514
♪<i> Not even easy to outsmart ♪</i>

11:55.581 --> 11:58.384
<i>♪ I'll have to click and hold ♪</i>

11:58.451 --> 12:00.686
<i>♪ And bold ♪</i>

12:00.753 --> 12:04.356
<i>♪ Delightful ♪</i>

12:04.423 --> 12:12.364
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:13.599 --> 12:15.034
- Okay, guys.

12:15.101 --> 12:16.969
Now that you've been born,
what should we do?

12:17.036 --> 12:18.704
Any ideas, Little Jeremy?

12:18.771 --> 12:21.707
"Oh, well, I--I don't know."

12:21.774 --> 12:24.110
It's cool, man.
How about you, Technobear?

12:24.176 --> 12:27.847
"Yo Dawg, I think we should
drop that bass, Dawg."

12:27.913 --> 12:30.516
Ooh, a party sounds delightful.

12:30.583 --> 12:34.453
"Oh! Oh, Harvey,
can I be the DJ?"

12:34.520 --> 12:36.088
Of course you can, bud.

12:36.155 --> 12:37.723
Boop!

12:37.790 --> 12:38.924
<i>[upbeat music plays]</i>

12:38.991 --> 12:39.725
Yeah!

12:39.792 --> 12:40.726
Go DJ Dade!

12:40.793 --> 12:43.729
[laughter]

12:43.796 --> 12:46.365
<i>♪</i> ♪

12:46.432 --> 12:49.268
- Come back here with my
underpants, you monsters!

12:49.335 --> 12:50.736
I only have one!

12:50.803 --> 12:53.439
Oh, wow, it's sunny out here.

12:53.506 --> 12:54.573
Phew, that's better.

12:54.640 --> 12:55.808
<i>♪</i> ♪

12:55.875 --> 12:57.576
Ugh!
Is that rock 'n' roll?

12:57.643 --> 13:02.381
That music's for demons.

13:02.448 --> 13:05.050
Kinda catchy though.

13:05.117 --> 13:07.520
Eh, there's no one lookin'.

13:07.586 --> 13:09.889
Yeah!
Uh-huh, come on!

13:09.955 --> 13:11.657
Uh!
Uh-huh!

13:11.724 --> 13:14.593
{\an3}Whoo hoo!

13:14.660 --> 13:16.162
{\an3}Oh my gosh,
I'm feelin' it.

13:16.228 --> 13:17.029
- Huh?

13:17.096 --> 13:19.131
{\an3}- Whoo!
Uh-huh!

13:19.198 --> 13:23.402
- Wait a minute,
is the doll controlling Dade?

13:23.469 --> 13:26.739
Whoa!

13:26.805 --> 13:29.475
[buzzing]

13:29.542 --> 13:31.177
[panting]

13:31.243 --> 13:33.012
{\an3}- So, what do you want us
to see again?

13:33.078 --> 13:35.681
- I like it
when we all hold hands.

13:35.748 --> 13:40.419
{\an1}- Listen. Nobody else can know
what I'm about to show you.

13:40.486 --> 13:42.221
Look!

13:42.288 --> 13:43.856
both: Whoa!

13:43.923 --> 13:45.457
{\an1}- They're like
little bug people!

13:45.524 --> 13:46.492
{\an1}- Close.

13:46.559 --> 13:47.927
It's a miniature recreation

13:47.993 --> 13:50.796
{\an1}of all the citizens
of Little Bark Grove!

13:50.863 --> 13:52.898
I made little dolls of everyone.

13:52.965 --> 13:55.501
See, here's you guys.

13:55.568 --> 13:57.836
And here's Rooter and Piri Piri.

13:57.903 --> 13:59.705
They like to be
next to each other.

13:59.772 --> 14:01.140
I even made this guy.

14:01.207 --> 14:03.108
- Who's that?
- I don't really know.

14:03.175 --> 14:05.077
But I see him in the background
sometimes.

14:05.144 --> 14:08.280
{\an3}- Wow! So, do we like,
step on 'em or--

14:08.347 --> 14:09.381
- No, no, no.

14:09.448 --> 14:11.283
Okay, I have this theory.

14:11.350 --> 14:14.019
I think the dolls have
some sort of special power.

14:14.086 --> 14:15.287
Whatever happens to the doll

14:15.354 --> 14:18.924
happens to the person
in real life.

14:18.991 --> 14:20.859
Here, watch this.

14:24.029 --> 14:26.298
{\an1}No Foo,
it's going the other way!

14:26.365 --> 14:29.068
- Oh.

14:29.134 --> 14:32.338
{\an1}- See?
I think they're magic!

14:32.404 --> 14:34.173
Foo, it stopped.

14:34.240 --> 14:35.207
- Oh, whoops.

14:35.274 --> 14:36.275
Hey!

14:36.342 --> 14:37.543
I stopped too!

14:37.610 --> 14:39.378
Maybe it is magic!

14:39.445 --> 14:42.348
- Let me see my doll.

14:42.414 --> 14:43.849
{\an3}Ow!
Oh, my gosh.

14:43.916 --> 14:46.452
{\an3}I smacked my head
with my doll's head,

14:46.518 --> 14:47.920
and mine hurts too!

14:47.987 --> 14:50.022
{\an1}- Okay, that's it.
That proves it.

14:50.089 --> 14:52.458
- Wow, magic dolls.

14:52.524 --> 14:55.194
I guess my love
just gave 'em power.

14:55.261 --> 14:59.331
- So, like, we have dolls
of everyone in town, right?

14:59.398 --> 15:01.634
Hmmmm...

15:01.700 --> 15:04.536
<i>♪</i> ♪

15:04.603 --> 15:08.140
[laughter]

15:08.207 --> 15:10.843
<i>♪</i> ♪

15:10.909 --> 15:13.946
- Oh-hohoho!

15:14.013 --> 15:16.815
<i>- [beeps]</i>
<i>Declined. Insufficient funds.</i>

15:16.882 --> 15:17.950
- Oh, no.

15:18.017 --> 15:19.752
You let it happen again.

15:19.818 --> 15:22.554
Stupid, stupid Jeremy.

15:22.621 --> 15:24.189
{\an3}[sobbing]

15:24.256 --> 15:26.425
- Jeremy looks really sad.

15:26.492 --> 15:29.461
{\an3}Maybe we can use this doll
to cheer him up.

15:29.528 --> 15:30.963
There we go.

15:31.030 --> 15:35.200
- [sobbing uncontrollably]

15:35.267 --> 15:37.703
- Hey--oh, what?

15:37.770 --> 15:40.105
[excited yelping]

15:40.172 --> 15:42.441
Oh boy oh boy oh--!

15:42.508 --> 15:43.876
- Yay!
We did it!

15:43.942 --> 15:45.411
all: Magic!

15:45.477 --> 15:46.845
- Ahhh.

15:46.912 --> 15:48.947
I'll think I'll treat myself
to another.

15:49.014 --> 15:50.683
<i>- Card declined.</i>

15:50.749 --> 15:51.684
- Oh.

15:51.750 --> 15:53.018
- Kratz...

15:53.085 --> 15:55.754
What does he like to do?

15:55.821 --> 15:59.425
[gasps]
He likes to sit!

15:59.491 --> 16:01.694
The magic continues!

16:01.760 --> 16:03.295
- Eww.
Princess?

16:03.362 --> 16:05.064
I don't want to magic her.

16:05.130 --> 16:07.700
{\an1}- Hey, I wanna see
what you nerds are doing.

16:07.766 --> 16:10.602
- Good-bye!

16:10.669 --> 16:12.838
- Ugh, you're lame.
I'm leaving.

16:12.905 --> 16:14.973
- I love these dolls.

16:15.040 --> 16:16.208
- Still sitting.

16:16.275 --> 16:18.844
Magic!

16:18.911 --> 16:19.878
{\an1}- Ow, ow.

16:19.945 --> 16:22.214
Why does this keep happening?

16:22.281 --> 16:23.649
- Whoa.

16:23.716 --> 16:25.351
[laughing]

16:25.417 --> 16:28.454
- [both giggling]

16:28.520 --> 16:31.523
[all laughing]

16:31.590 --> 16:32.925
- Okay, I have to admit,

16:32.991 --> 16:35.160
these dolls are the best things
I've ever made.

16:35.227 --> 16:37.830
I think I'll give myself
a pat on the back.

16:37.896 --> 16:39.465
Pat pat.

16:39.531 --> 16:40.632
Pat pat pat.

16:40.699 --> 16:42.468
{\an1}- If only we had
tiny little houses

16:42.534 --> 16:44.803
for our tiny little dolls.

16:44.870 --> 16:48.240
{\an3}- Ooh!

16:48.307 --> 16:49.475
There we go.

16:49.541 --> 16:52.044
And put us here.

16:52.111 --> 16:54.046
That's pretty much
the entire town.

16:54.113 --> 16:55.347
The dolls have a whole

16:55.414 --> 16:58.717
Little Little Bark Grove
of their own now.

16:58.784 --> 17:00.919
{\an1}- Wait, so if the dolls
are magic,

17:00.986 --> 17:02.788
is the town magic too?

17:02.855 --> 17:03.989
- Yeah.

17:04.056 --> 17:06.592
I guess it is.

17:06.657 --> 17:07.726
{\an3}- Quick!
Grab ze safe!

17:07.792 --> 17:09.595
- [babbling]

17:09.661 --> 17:11.029
- Of course it's heavy!

17:11.096 --> 17:12.664
[both grunting]

17:12.731 --> 17:16.068
{\an3}- [sigh] Out of ze way.
I'll do it!

17:16.135 --> 17:19.805
{\an1}- Okay, little me,
what am I thinking about?

17:19.872 --> 17:22.007
- Scatter! Scatter!
Whoa!

17:22.074 --> 17:24.777
- Oh my gosh,
Foo's doll!

17:24.843 --> 17:28.680
If your doll had been hurt,
you could have gotten hurt!

17:28.747 --> 17:30.482
- I'll be more careful.

17:30.549 --> 17:32.651
[gasps]
Look!

17:32.718 --> 17:34.186
{\an1}- Oh, man!

17:34.253 --> 17:36.288
This branch almost tore a hole
through my tiny house!

17:36.355 --> 17:38.390
That could have been really bad.

17:38.457 --> 17:41.727
I would hate for something
to happen to my real house.

17:41.794 --> 17:44.830
We're gonna to have to take
this magic stuff more seriously.

17:44.897 --> 17:46.331
We're responsible

17:46.398 --> 17:48.667
{\an3}for lots of peoples' homes
and well-being now.

17:48.734 --> 17:51.003
{\an3}We got to guard this place
with our lives.

17:51.069 --> 17:52.504
- Don't worry, dude.

17:52.571 --> 17:54.540
Ain't no one gonna to mess
with Little Little Bark

17:54.606 --> 17:55.641
while we're around.

17:55.707 --> 17:56.708
{\an1}- Yeah!

17:56.775 --> 17:58.911
- [giggling]

17:58.977 --> 18:01.947
{\an3}- Oh.
Hey, Michelle.

18:02.014 --> 18:03.048
[all gasping]

18:03.115 --> 18:04.483
{\an3}- Michelle!
Wait!

18:04.550 --> 18:05.918
- Oooooh!

18:05.984 --> 18:07.119
[evil chuckles]

18:07.186 --> 18:10.322
<i>[ominous music]</i>

18:10.389 --> 18:17.429
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:17.496 --> 18:18.430
- Nooo!

18:18.497 --> 18:19.565
- [chuckles]

18:19.631 --> 18:21.433
{\an1}- [panting]
Oof!

18:21.500 --> 18:22.901
Michelle, stop!

18:22.968 --> 18:28.841
<i>♪</i> ♪

18:28.907 --> 18:29.875
[grunts]

18:29.942 --> 18:30.909
Oh, no!

18:30.976 --> 18:32.244
Not the orphanage!

18:32.311 --> 18:34.680
They've already had it
hard enough!

18:34.746 --> 18:42.120
<i>♪</i> ♪

18:42.187 --> 18:43.655
[sizzling]

18:45.657 --> 18:47.192
- [sneezes]

18:47.259 --> 18:49.728
[carefree giggles]

18:49.795 --> 18:50.929
{\an1}- Wow.

18:50.996 --> 18:52.231
{\an1}Who'da thought
something so adorable

18:52.297 --> 18:54.066
could do so much destruction?

18:54.132 --> 18:56.602
- You guys,
this is all our fault!

18:56.668 --> 19:01.039
We just led Little Bark
into an untimely doom!

19:01.106 --> 19:03.575
- We sure did.

19:03.642 --> 19:06.211
Well, we might as well go tell
everyone they're goners.

19:06.278 --> 19:07.646
- Everyone!
Run for your lives!

19:07.713 --> 19:08.947
Run!

19:09.014 --> 19:10.816
Or we're all gonna die!

19:10.883 --> 19:12.084
- What?
- Why?

19:12.150 --> 19:13.952
- You're all in danger!

19:14.019 --> 19:15.487
Littlebark is about to be
destroyed!

19:15.554 --> 19:17.890
Save yourselves
while you still can!

19:17.956 --> 19:19.958
We're all doomed!

19:20.025 --> 19:21.460
- Out of my way!

19:21.527 --> 19:23.862
[all screaming]

19:23.929 --> 19:25.030
<i>♪</i> ♪

19:25.097 --> 19:26.865
- Hurry up, you guys!

19:26.932 --> 19:29.868
We're getting punished because
I danced to rock 'n' roll.

19:29.935 --> 19:31.136
Oof!

19:31.203 --> 19:32.404
all: [gasping]
Dade!

19:32.471 --> 19:33.872
{\an3}- No!
Leave him!

19:33.939 --> 19:36.708
That's what he'd want!

19:36.775 --> 19:37.910
- Wade!
Come back!

19:37.976 --> 19:39.111
- Hurry up, honey!

19:39.177 --> 19:40.245
- Let me just lock the door.

19:40.312 --> 19:41.713
- That doesn't matter anymore.

19:41.780 --> 19:44.349
- You're right.
You're all that matters now.

19:44.416 --> 19:45.951
- All clear!
C'mon, Ma!

19:46.018 --> 19:47.986
- Wheel me to the good china!

19:48.053 --> 19:49.955
- I'm gonna try
to climb to safety!

19:50.022 --> 19:51.290
Just toss...

19:51.356 --> 19:53.625
Junior up when I get there!

19:53.692 --> 19:57.496
- Oh my gosh,
it's all coming true!

19:57.563 --> 19:58.497
Aah!

19:58.564 --> 20:01.700
I got to fix this!
Guys?

20:01.767 --> 20:06.638
- Sorry, we just got caught up
in the destruction.

20:06.705 --> 20:11.143
- I wish little me
had never been born.

20:11.209 --> 20:12.144
That's it!

20:12.210 --> 20:13.879
Maybe I can end this madness

20:13.946 --> 20:17.916
if I destroy the doll
that started it all.

20:17.983 --> 20:19.751
{\an3}- No!

20:19.818 --> 20:23.622
{\an1}- But, Harvey, if you break
the doll, what'll happen to you?

20:23.689 --> 20:24.623
- I don't know.

20:24.690 --> 20:27.793
But it's a risk I have to take.

20:27.859 --> 20:29.995
It's time to be delivered

20:30.062 --> 20:32.931
to the angel of death.

20:32.998 --> 20:36.335
- [sinister laughing]

20:36.401 --> 20:37.669
- All right, Michelle,

20:37.736 --> 20:40.606
in order to save our town,
I need you to---

20:40.672 --> 20:41.740
[inhales]

20:41.807 --> 20:44.309
Destroy my doll.

20:44.376 --> 20:45.644
I know this is gonna be
hard for you

20:45.711 --> 20:47.512
because I'm your big brother.

20:47.579 --> 20:50.048
And I know you love me and don't
wanna hurt me, but--

20:50.115 --> 20:51.216
- Dude, she already started.

20:51.283 --> 20:52.951
- Ah! Ah! Ah!

20:53.018 --> 20:55.821
[babbling]

20:55.887 --> 20:59.625
- Oh, it hurts!
Ah ha!

20:59.691 --> 21:00.959
This is it.

21:01.026 --> 21:02.294
- Harvey?
- Yeah, Fee?

21:02.361 --> 21:03.795
- When you're gone...

21:03.862 --> 21:05.130
can I have your bicycle?

21:05.197 --> 21:06.565
- Totally.

21:06.632 --> 21:07.466
{\an3}- I just...

21:07.532 --> 21:09.234
love that bike so much.

21:09.301 --> 21:12.204
- [babbling]

21:12.270 --> 21:16.975
- [groaning]

21:17.042 --> 21:18.977
Aah!

21:19.044 --> 21:21.780
<i>♪</i> ♪

21:22.481 --> 21:25.484
[birds chirp]

21:25.550 --> 21:27.753
Huh?

21:27.819 --> 21:29.321
I--I'm okay!

21:29.388 --> 21:31.223
I'm okay!

21:31.289 --> 21:32.224
[laughing]

21:32.290 --> 21:33.225
- It worked, dude!

21:33.291 --> 21:34.860
The magic spell is broken!

21:34.926 --> 21:36.862
- And it's a good thing,
'cause I just ate my doll.

21:36.928 --> 21:38.563
I taste like pennies.

21:38.630 --> 21:40.399
{\an3}- I'm so glad we were able
to save the town

21:40.465 --> 21:41.900
from being destroyed.

21:41.967 --> 21:43.702
{\an1}- Do you think they're gonna
give us a parade, Harvey?

21:43.769 --> 21:45.003
{\an3}- Maybe!

21:45.070 --> 21:47.572
{\an3}We really did a great thing
for everyone.

21:47.639 --> 21:49.808
Something really special.

21:49.875 --> 21:52.811
[all screaming]

21:52.878 --> 21:59.484
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:01.853 --> 22:04.790
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

22:04.856 --> 22:12.798
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:25.277 --> 22:30.782
<i>♪</i> ♪
